1
00:00:00,547 --> 00:00:03,840
I just don't want to
go to Nakhon Nayok.

2
00:00:05,273 --> 00:00:06,476
Grandma's house...

3
00:00:08,119 --> 00:00:09,360
Dong Lakhon.

4
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:11,520
Dad.

5
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:14,680
Come to Grandma, please!

6
00:00:15,127 --> 00:00:17,023
Ohn, can you hear me?

7
00:00:17,023 --> 00:00:18,143
Ohn.

8
00:00:19,299 --> 00:00:21,120
Dad's right here. Can you hear me?

9
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:23,160
We're all right here with you.

10
00:00:43,533 --> 00:00:46,400
"Tonight, we can't sleep."

11
00:01:11,406 --> 00:01:12,933
If I still can't draw,

12
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,746
then I'll really give up.

13
00:01:15,746 --> 00:01:17,560
Give up?

14
00:01:18,083 --> 00:01:21,040
I told you,
I'll never give up on us.

15
00:01:21,568 --> 00:01:24,744
Jeez, Old Man,
I was just talking about work.

16
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,100
Go to sleep.

17
00:01:51,810 --> 00:01:54,160
Ohn, is something wrong?

18
00:01:57,802 --> 00:02:00,560
- What should I do?
- Hmm?

19
00:02:03,305 --> 00:02:05,680
I have no energy to work at all.

20
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,640
Mmm.

21
00:02:16,533 --> 00:02:20,240
I don't have the energy
to keep job hunting either.

22
00:02:20,713 --> 00:02:21,859
Is that so wrong?

23
00:02:26,248 --> 00:02:28,069
- How about this?
- Hmm?

24
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:31,000
Why don't we go
on a trip to recharge?

25
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:36,960
Actually, never mind.

26
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,306
We need to save money, right?

27
00:02:39,830 --> 00:02:40,830
Mmm.

28
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:44,160
But for now...

29
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,880
we can do this.

30
00:02:54,899 --> 00:02:57,080
What are you doing, Jee?

31
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,200
That tickles.

32
00:03:34,393 --> 00:03:35,639
- Jee.
- Hmm?

33
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,720
Who's messaging you
this late at night?

34
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:48,120
I got a job interview.

35
00:03:49,210 --> 00:03:50,440
- What?
- Mmm.

36
00:03:50,464 --> 00:03:52,175
For real?

37
00:03:52,199 --> 00:03:54,680
Congratulations!

38
00:03:54,793 --> 00:03:57,760
- Yay!
- Yay!

39
00:03:59,352 --> 00:04:02,480
That's one person who's
going to sleep well tonight.

40
00:04:02,505 --> 00:04:04,680
Definitely.

41
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:11,320
Yay...

42
00:04:18,538 --> 00:04:20,960
"Even though I feel burned out,"

43
00:04:21,992 --> 00:04:24,000
"being able to lie here
next to him like this"

44
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,800
"feels like a dream, doesn't it?"

45
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:30,766
"But why can't I sleep?"

46
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,564
"I can't sleep either,"

47
00:04:44,564 --> 00:04:46,588
"because I've been banned
by my friends."

48
00:04:52,502 --> 00:04:54,760
It's time for bed, sweetie.

49
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,082
Okay, Mom.

50
00:05:08,633 --> 00:05:10,969
"If they want to ban me, let them."

51
00:05:11,688 --> 00:05:12,720
"I don't care."

52
00:05:13,462 --> 00:05:15,360
"My dream is to be a Sigma."

53
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:28,033
- Grandma?
- Yes?

54
00:05:28,033 --> 00:05:29,090
Let's start now.

55
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,640
Go ahead and ask away.

56
00:05:32,158 --> 00:05:33,480
Okay, Grandma.

57
00:05:36,414 --> 00:05:37,414
Action!

58
00:05:38,983 --> 00:05:41,160
When you were a kid,
what did you want to be?

59
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,473
I dreamed of...

60
00:05:46,173 --> 00:05:49,440
Last night, I dreamed of
getting a massive gold chain.

61
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,240
It was absolutely huge!

62
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,720
I think I'm about to
have some incredible luck.

63
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:56,004
- That's not it, Grandma.
- Oh?

64
00:05:56,004 --> 00:05:57,711
I didn't mean
your dream from last night.

65
00:05:57,711 --> 00:06:01,703
I mean back when you
were a child around my age.

66
00:06:02,159 --> 00:06:04,032
What did you want to be
when you grew up?

67
00:06:05,248 --> 00:06:06,840
Oh...

68
00:06:07,608 --> 00:06:11,725
What did I dream of being
when I was a kid, right?

69
00:06:12,451 --> 00:06:14,080
Um...

70
00:06:16,236 --> 00:06:18,760
Uh...

71
00:06:21,850 --> 00:06:24,200
What was it I wanted to be?

72
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,080
- Grandma.
- Huh?

73
00:06:31,063 --> 00:06:34,002
I still can't think of it.

74
00:06:34,515 --> 00:06:36,393
In that case, let's just
change the question.

75
00:06:36,393 --> 00:06:38,480
Good idea, sweetie.
Ask something else.

76
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:39,618
Changing the question.

77
00:06:39,618 --> 00:06:42,817
Do you still have any dreams now?

78
00:06:43,707 --> 00:06:46,374
I'm over 70 years old now.

79
00:06:46,374 --> 00:06:49,260
Every day I wake up and I can walk,

80
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:51,680
go places, and do everything,

81
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:54,247
I feel like I've already
won the lottery.

82
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:58,000
But if I could have one dream now,

83
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,367
I wish I could make it
to the bathroom in time.

84
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:02,293
That would be wonderful.

85
00:07:03,304 --> 00:07:06,150
Just laughing like this,
I'm already about to pee myself.

86
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,580
- Grandma!
- Yes?

87
00:07:08,580 --> 00:07:09,909
Stop joking around.

88
00:07:09,909 --> 00:07:11,916
I really have to go.

89
00:07:12,383 --> 00:07:14,383
Can I go pee?

90
00:07:14,706 --> 00:07:16,720
Am I missing all the fun?

91
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,727
Uncle Ohn, please help me!

92
00:07:19,727 --> 00:07:20,967
Help with what?

93
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:23,280
Whatever I ask,
Grandma won't answer.

94
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,440
She dodges the questions,
and then...

95
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,920
she keeps joking around.

96
00:07:28,939 --> 00:07:30,992
- Ow!
- Hi, Mom.

97
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:32,257
Hello, son.

98
00:07:32,257 --> 00:07:36,840
Ikkyu, you see Uncle Ohn, and
you start tattling non-stop.

99
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:46,707
Why don't you open the door
to let some Qi energy in?

100
00:07:46,707 --> 00:07:49,400
Staying in the dark like this
is bad for your health, you know?

101
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:53,400
I'm so glad you're free to help me.

102
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:55,840
Aren't you busy with work?

103
00:07:57,200 --> 00:08:01,320
Work is not too busy.

104
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:07,960
I thought you wanted me
to help film a dance clip.

105
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:09,760
We'll definitely do that.

106
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:11,985
But I have to do
my interview project first.

107
00:08:11,985 --> 00:08:12,985
Hmm?

108
00:08:13,981 --> 00:08:16,441
Here, Once Upon a Dream.

109
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:21,720
Whoa, that's a very chic name.

110
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,539
What does it mean?

111
00:08:24,591 --> 00:08:27,391
It means,
once upon a time, I had a dream.

112
00:08:27,391 --> 00:08:28,440
Mmm.

113
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:31,200
The teacher wants us to interview
the adults in our family

114
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:33,280
on the topic of childhood dreams.

115
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:38,280
I'll be the Director, and
you'll be the Assistant Director.

116
00:08:38,955 --> 00:08:41,320
You'll be the Camera Assistant,
help plan the trip

117
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,547
- Buy us pizza, and...
- Whoa, wait, wait.

118
00:08:43,547 --> 00:08:45,680
Calm down there, Mr. Director.

119
00:08:46,737 --> 00:08:50,320
I don't mind
being the Assistant Director

120
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,744
but why do we have to travel?

121
00:08:53,744 --> 00:08:55,268
And what's with the pizza?

122
00:08:55,268 --> 00:08:57,624
I thought you were
interviewing people at home.

123
00:08:57,624 --> 00:08:59,011
That's right.

124
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,240
Grandma, Mom, and you are family.

125
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:05,567
But I want to
interview your friends, too.

126
00:09:05,567 --> 00:09:07,127
And Uncle Kong as well.

127
00:09:07,127 --> 00:09:08,860
I want to know

128
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:12,140
if I grow up to be like you guys,
can my dreams actually come true?

129
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:16,000
That's quite an impressive idea.

130
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:19,901
Is this what 6th graders
nowadays are capable of?

131
00:09:20,269 --> 00:09:22,600
It's because I'm smart.
I nailed the assignment.

132
00:09:23,587 --> 00:09:25,987
It's a group project,
but I'm doing it all by myself.

133
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,200
Is that even allowed?

134
00:09:29,227 --> 00:09:33,021
Don't your friends or your teacher
mind that you're doing it alone?

135
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,680
My friends seem a bit confused.

136
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:38,720
But the teacher said if I think
I can do it, then go ahead.

137
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:40,760
Mmm...

138
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:47,080
Okay. Give me some time
to set things up first.

139
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,920
Who do you want to interview first?

140
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:51,840
Uncle Jee first.

141
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,180
Interviewing Uncle Jee, too?

142
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,480
Here you are.

143
00:10:04,398 --> 00:10:05,400
Hello, Uncle Jee.

144
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,440
Hello, dear.

145
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:08,120
You look very handsome today.

146
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:11,000
Thank you so much, my love.

147
00:10:11,098 --> 00:10:12,520
- Mmm...
- Mmm...

148
00:10:12,545 --> 00:10:16,782
She complimented you a little,
and now she is your love?

149
00:10:18,517 --> 00:10:22,040
Ikkyu, the reason Uncle Jee
dressed so nice today

150
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:24,680
is because he has
a special appointment.

151
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:28,120
Yes, I'm very excited today.

152
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:32,280
It's my first ever
for an online job interview.

153
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:36,200
I thought you dressed up
for my project.

154
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:57,953
Hello?

155
00:10:57,953 --> 00:11:00,240
Hello? Hi, hi. Hello!

156
00:11:05,922 --> 00:11:09,429
Well, this outfit
is for your project.

157
00:11:09,429 --> 00:11:11,800
Then I'll head straight
into the interview.

158
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:15,600
Is it hard to find a job
at your old age, Uncle Jee?

159
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,600
Ouch!

160
00:11:18,627 --> 00:11:19,707
Old?

161
00:11:20,611 --> 00:11:22,219
Well, it's not easy.

162
00:11:22,219 --> 00:11:24,404
There are so many talented
young people these days.

163
00:11:25,114 --> 00:11:28,051
- Ikkyu, can you do me a favor?
- Yes.

164
00:11:28,486 --> 00:11:29,946
Please stop using the word "old."

165
00:11:30,318 --> 00:11:32,805
It's totally killing my confidence.

166
00:11:32,805 --> 00:11:36,520
Sorry. Let's call it
"late adolescence" instead.

167
00:11:37,179 --> 00:11:41,040
I didn't teach him that one.

168
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:46,493
Like uncle, like nephew, huh?

169
00:11:46,493 --> 00:11:49,040
Alright, let's get on
with the interview.

170
00:11:49,846 --> 00:11:51,226
Are you ready, Uncle Jee?

171
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,480
Yes.

172
00:11:57,323 --> 00:11:59,856
"To me, Uncle Jee, or Jira"

173
00:11:59,856 --> 00:12:01,960
"is the person who best fits
the word 'Perfect'."

174
00:12:02,491 --> 00:12:04,252
"I wonder what kind
of childhood dreams"

175
00:12:04,252 --> 00:12:06,438
"a perfect person
like Uncle Jee had."

176
00:12:06,438 --> 00:12:07,760
And... Action!

177
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:13,120
My childhood dreams...

178
00:12:13,636 --> 00:12:16,480
was to be a doctor.

179
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:21,520
No one told me to;
I thought of it myself.

180
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,960
I wanted to
be a doctor was because

181
00:12:25,336 --> 00:12:29,139
they seem so smart and cool
in their white coats,

182
00:12:29,139 --> 00:12:31,146
and they help people.

183
00:12:31,146 --> 00:12:33,240
Most importantly,
I thought they'd be rich.

184
00:12:35,499 --> 00:12:37,116
I also had another dream...

185
00:12:38,187 --> 00:12:39,187
to...

186
00:12:41,272 --> 00:12:42,272
Get married.

187
00:12:43,124 --> 00:12:44,124
Have children.

188
00:12:44,851 --> 00:12:46,240
Have a family.

189
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,375
Have dinner together as a family.

190
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:01,040
Why didn't you become a doctor?

191
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,880
Are you sad about it now?

192
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,400
Well, I didn't pass
the entrance exam.

193
00:13:08,489 --> 00:13:09,989
But it's okay, because

194
00:13:09,989 --> 00:13:13,240
I got into
the Faculty of Accounting,

195
00:13:13,583 --> 00:13:15,360
which was my third choice.

196
00:13:15,951 --> 00:13:18,304
And university life was great.

197
00:13:18,304 --> 00:13:21,920
It was so much fun
that I didn't have time to be sad.

198
00:13:22,597 --> 00:13:24,120
And then I discovered that

199
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:28,320
I could be talented and cool
in my own career path, too.

200
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,080
That counts as...

201
00:13:31,326 --> 00:13:34,115
one of my successful dreams.

202
00:13:34,858 --> 00:13:35,864
Mmm-hmm.

203
00:13:36,391 --> 00:13:37,931
Even if I am unemployed right now.

204
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:41,880
But...

205
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:47,680
some things didn't turn out
the way I thought or dreamed.

206
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,440
Like...

207
00:13:50,424 --> 00:13:52,160
Having a boyfriend.

208
00:13:56,240 --> 00:14:00,720
My family and I aren't
as close as we used to be.

209
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:02,280
We didn't fight.

210
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,760
But it's as if we are...

211
00:14:06,790 --> 00:14:08,200
growing more distant.

212
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:10,440
It might be because

213
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,120
my parents didn't get
what they had hoped for.

214
00:14:15,186 --> 00:14:16,493
Which is something I have to...

215
00:14:17,914 --> 00:14:19,960
accept and wait...

216
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:23,573
until they eventually accept it.

217
00:14:24,386 --> 00:14:27,560
Then they'll get
what they were hoping for.

218
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:33,160
And do you have a dream now?

219
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,200
I do.

220
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:40,280
My dream is to still
be working, doing anything

221
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,002
that is meaningful each day,

222
00:14:43,002 --> 00:14:45,773
alongside someone
who truly loves me.

223
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,665
- Cut!
- Mmm.

224
00:14:55,278 --> 00:14:58,080
Just in time for my job interview.

225
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:02,600
You're starting
a new dream, aren't you?

226
00:15:02,970 --> 00:15:04,860
Mmm, that's the best way to put it.

227
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:07,413
- Well, I'll go follow my dream.
- Okay.

228
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,913
Here I go.

229
00:15:10,913 --> 00:15:13,280
It's almost time.

230
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,440
Alright.

231
00:15:23,166 --> 00:15:24,166
Test, test.

232
00:15:39,590 --> 00:15:42,040
Hello, Mr. Jira.
Can you hear me okay?

233
00:15:42,954 --> 00:15:44,600
Hello. Yes, I can hear you fine.

234
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:48,480
- Here.
- Thank you.

235
00:15:51,026 --> 00:15:53,000
Come on. I'm ready.

236
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:57,800
And... Action!

237
00:15:59,755 --> 00:16:03,120
When I was a kid, I wanted
to be a national volleyball player,

238
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,293
to take the team to the Olympics.

239
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:09,940
- Come on, Spectrum Fabulous!
- Spectrum Fabulous!

240
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:12,320
Woo! Woo!

241
00:16:13,546 --> 00:16:15,640
- Spectrum Fabulous!
- Spectrum Fabulous!

242
00:16:17,003 --> 00:16:19,476
Back in the day,
we were so into it.

243
00:16:19,476 --> 00:16:21,510
Everyone was totally obsessed.

244
00:16:21,510 --> 00:16:25,243
Wow, that name
was really something!

245
00:16:25,243 --> 00:16:28,440
It sounded like a girl group,
like a gang of angels.

246
00:16:29,991 --> 00:16:33,520
Honestly, our Fab team
was actually very good.

247
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,053
But we ran into various problems.

248
00:16:36,053 --> 00:16:38,668
So we never
made it to the Olympics.

249
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:43,600
But the dream I wanted
more than anything else...

250
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,520
was to be a singer.

251
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:54,233
Back then, a Luk Thung band
came to play near my house.

252
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:56,560
It was my mother
who took me to see them.

253
00:16:57,120 --> 00:17:00,487
I remember it so clearly;
there were so many people that day.

254
00:17:00,487 --> 00:17:03,400
The lights, the colors, the sound,
it was absolutely grand.

255
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:07,320
I chose to go stand
right by the speakers.

256
00:17:07,895 --> 00:17:12,400
I wanted that booming bass
to hit me in the face and body.

257
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,160
And I kept dancing there.

258
00:17:15,165 --> 00:17:18,680
When my favorite song came on,
the feeling was just incredible.

259
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,520
That was the first time

260
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:26,280
that I saw a real singer.

261
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,120
Got to see the dancers.

262
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:31,800
Got to see
the musicians playing live.

263
00:17:33,030 --> 00:17:34,960
My heart was beating so fast.

264
00:17:35,518 --> 00:17:37,240
And I told myself...

265
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:40,360
"I'm going to be a singer."

266
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,360
But when...

267
00:17:45,402 --> 00:17:46,402
I grew up,

268
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:50,000
nothing was
as simple as I had planned.

269
00:18:00,216 --> 00:18:01,560
In those days...

270
00:18:03,257 --> 00:18:05,080
a singer with a sweet voice

271
00:18:05,849 --> 00:18:06,960
who was gay

272
00:18:08,064 --> 00:18:12,160
they said the image
wasn't suitable for a singer

273
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:13,680
that people wanted to see.

274
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:18,280
Record labels
wouldn't sign you easily.

275
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:22,560
And the stage
wasn't as open as it is today.

276
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,640
So my dream...

277
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,600
slowly faded away.

278
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,920
What did you do next?

279
00:18:36,977 --> 00:18:40,080
I think now
I've found where I belong.

280
00:18:41,305 --> 00:18:43,185
It's right here behind the scenes.

281
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:47,080
I want to build a stage.

282
00:18:47,721 --> 00:18:50,840
Create a space and a path
for the new generation of singers.

283
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:55,280
So that queer singers
will have a place to sing.

284
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:56,800
Honestly,

285
00:18:57,385 --> 00:18:59,680
their voice can be any way at all,

286
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:04,440
as long as it's their voice,
their true identity.

287
00:19:05,675 --> 00:19:07,482
I want to support them

288
00:19:07,482 --> 00:19:10,922
just like the support
I received from my mother

289
00:19:10,922 --> 00:19:13,120
and from my friends.

290
00:19:16,420 --> 00:19:18,400
"Uncle Thai concluded that"

291
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,467
"dreams can change anytime."

292
00:19:20,467 --> 00:19:23,127
"It's okay no matter
how many times your dream changes."

293
00:19:23,127 --> 00:19:26,160
"As long as we still love to dream,
we can always start a new one."

294
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,080
Cut!

295
00:19:35,265 --> 00:19:36,600
Thank you so much, Uncle Thai.

296
00:19:37,340 --> 00:19:38,340
You're welcome, dear.

297
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,040
Are you ready?

298
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:51,840
And... Action!

299
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:54,653
When I was a kid,
I loved traditional dance.

300
00:19:54,653 --> 00:19:56,316
I wanted to be a star.

301
00:19:56,316 --> 00:19:58,733
I wanted to be beautiful,
and to have the spotlight on me.

302
00:19:58,733 --> 00:20:00,600
When I wore the dance costume,

303
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,980
I felt like I was a princess.

304
00:20:02,980 --> 00:20:05,280
So I thought, this is the dream.

305
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:10,378
To be up there performing on stage
with so many people

306
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:14,560
watching and paying attention.
It made me feel like I was shining.

307
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,256
But when I grew up,

308
00:20:17,256 --> 00:20:20,410
I realized that
I was a trans woman.

309
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:28,486
I understood then that
I could never be the leading lady.

310
00:20:29,653 --> 00:20:32,080
Because there's
a standard of beauty

311
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:34,720
that I didn't fit into that box.

312
00:20:35,985 --> 00:20:37,235
But I was lucky.

313
00:20:37,892 --> 00:20:39,320
I found something I love

314
00:20:39,809 --> 00:20:41,476
when I was at
the College of Fine Arts.

315
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:44,421
I fell in love with tattoo art.

316
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:48,240
It's truly beautiful.

317
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:52,760
Tattooing isn't just about
patterns on the skin.

318
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:56,080
It's a way for us to
tell the world loudly and clearly

319
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,800
exactly who we are.

320
00:20:58,704 --> 00:21:00,400
So, I opened a tattoo parlor

321
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:02,880
which...

322
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,080
I am incredibly proud of.

323
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,960
Even though I didn't become a star,
it's perfectly fine.

324
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:13,400
I'm even more than a star now.

325
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:16,840
Customers love it;
they spread the word.

326
00:21:18,138 --> 00:21:19,511
I have fans

327
00:21:19,511 --> 00:21:21,191
who have been coming to me

328
00:21:21,191 --> 00:21:23,798
since their first tattoo
to their latest.

329
00:21:24,822 --> 00:21:26,502
I get to do what I love.

330
00:21:27,310 --> 00:21:28,960
And take care of those who...

331
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:33,166
love me for who I truly am.

332
00:21:35,682 --> 00:21:36,962
That's more than enough.

333
00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:39,760
And most importantly...

334
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:42,880
I get to be myself.

335
00:21:48,324 --> 00:21:49,360
Cut!

336
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:52,040
Was that okay?

337
00:21:53,129 --> 00:21:54,129
It was great!

338
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,387
Orange juice, dear.

339
00:22:10,387 --> 00:22:12,680
- Thank you, Auntie Nidnoy.
- Thank you.

340
00:22:15,281 --> 00:22:17,961
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

341
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,253
They are so lovely.

342
00:22:38,253 --> 00:22:39,568
Unlike anybody else,

343
00:22:39,568 --> 00:22:41,641
but you can tell
they really love each other.

344
00:22:41,641 --> 00:22:45,087
Yes, they love and understand
each other very much.

345
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:49,920
You're very lucky too
to have Uncle Jee.

346
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,900
You know everything, don't you?

347
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:57,346
Hurry up and pack your things,
you precocious little director.

348
00:23:06,079 --> 00:23:08,146
"Although Auntie Chon
didn't become a leading lady,"

349
00:23:08,146 --> 00:23:09,806
"she has a spotlight of her own."

350
00:23:09,806 --> 00:23:13,040
"And she gets to share that light
with those who truly see her."

351
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:38,840
Is this what you've had so far?

352
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:40,480
Yes, Uncle Ohn.

353
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:43,680
You edited this really fast.

354
00:23:48,944 --> 00:23:49,985
Uncle Ohn...

355
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:54,080
I never knew that for
the LGBTQ community in your time

356
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:55,880
some dreams were just impossible.

357
00:23:57,268 --> 00:24:00,840
Well, not all of them.

358
00:24:02,386 --> 00:24:04,120
Back then, that's just how it was.

359
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,840
Some dreams...

360
00:24:07,887 --> 00:24:09,800
were stopped
before they even began.

361
00:24:11,001 --> 00:24:13,080
But things have changed
a lot nowadays.

362
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,920
I just realized that

363
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:17,960
we might have to keep finding
new jobs like Uncle Jee.

364
00:24:18,415 --> 00:24:19,800
I guess I'm just used to

365
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,040
seeing Mom only work
as a civil servant all this time.

366
00:24:23,173 --> 00:24:27,320
Who told you that?
Your mom has done it all.

367
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:30,720
You could call her
a master salesperson.

368
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:35,613
When she was a kid,
she helped Grandma sell things.

369
00:24:36,149 --> 00:24:38,320
She made sandwiches
to sell at school.

370
00:24:38,860 --> 00:24:40,720
And once she grew up
and started working,

371
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,900
well, she'd find things to sell.

372
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:45,800
She'd pick mangoes
and sell at the office.

373
00:24:46,206 --> 00:24:48,984
And she even did direct sales
for a few different companies.

374
00:24:49,615 --> 00:24:52,120
Wow, was Mom struggling that much?

375
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,680
She saw Grandma working so hard.

376
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,160
So she wanted to
help earn some money.

377
00:24:58,715 --> 00:25:02,868
Since she was so good at selling,
she basically never stopped.

378
00:25:02,868 --> 00:25:04,421
When she was pregnant with you,

379
00:25:04,421 --> 00:25:06,888
she worked even harder,
finding more things to sell.

380
00:25:09,140 --> 00:25:12,336
Should I start
looking for a job now?

381
00:25:12,523 --> 00:25:13,523
Whoa there.

382
00:25:14,133 --> 00:25:15,340
Don't be dramatic.

383
00:25:15,340 --> 00:25:16,986
How about you
finish 6th grade first?

384
00:25:17,605 --> 00:25:21,207
Just knowing you want to help,
she would be incredibly happy.

385
00:25:24,235 --> 00:25:25,400
Mmm...

386
00:25:30,548 --> 00:25:32,640
And don't you want to
have kids of your own?

387
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:42,480
I'm indifferent about it.

388
00:25:43,540 --> 00:25:44,600
Not now.

389
00:25:45,264 --> 00:25:46,264
Mmm.

390
00:25:48,389 --> 00:25:49,509
What about getting married?

391
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:55,447
I think sometimes love

392
00:25:55,447 --> 00:25:58,600
doesn't necessarily
have to end in marriage.

393
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:05,040
Mmm...
Maybe this way is just as good.

394
00:26:07,276 --> 00:26:08,600
I think so.

395
00:26:14,608 --> 00:26:17,187
- Mom's calling.
- Hmm?

396
00:26:17,187 --> 00:26:18,320
Hurry up

397
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:20,420
before she sell us
like those mangoes.

398
00:26:20,420 --> 00:26:22,774
- Oh, no! Let's go!
- Quickly, Uncle Ohn!

399
00:26:22,774 --> 00:26:24,280
I don't want to be a mango either.

400
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:30,480
It shouldn't have rained.
Mom is probably stuck in traffic.

401
00:26:31,504 --> 00:26:33,351
When it rains,
traffic gets like this.

402
00:26:33,850 --> 00:26:36,410
But she will be here soon.

403
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,556
Ikkyu...

404
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,720
Look!

405
00:26:46,476 --> 00:26:47,522
Mmm...

406
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:52,960
Today we're here
to interview a special guest.

407
00:26:53,879 --> 00:26:56,320
A lost cat, but it has a collar.

408
00:26:56,921 --> 00:26:59,961
It looks like it could be
the heir to a billionaire.

409
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:04,227
Hello. My name is...

410
00:27:04,227 --> 00:27:06,042
Wait, I don't have a name yet.

411
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:11,240
But I dream of having
my own mackerel shop.

412
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,800
So that I'll never be hungry again.

413
00:27:16,754 --> 00:27:18,362
The fur is so soft.

414
00:27:18,387 --> 00:27:20,240
Are you lost, little one?

415
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:25,000
It looks very much
like a house cat.

416
00:27:25,585 --> 00:27:27,960
Look how soft the fur is.

417
00:27:28,331 --> 00:27:31,480
I also think it looks very clean.

418
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,080
It doesn't seem like a stray.

419
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,480
If that's the case...

420
00:27:36,153 --> 00:27:39,160
it's either lost
or might have been abandoned.

421
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,800
The interview isn't even over

422
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:45,486
and it's already about
to get a new home, everyone!

423
00:27:51,543 --> 00:27:52,753
Let's go home, sweetie.

424
00:27:56,228 --> 00:27:57,228
Hey!

425
00:27:58,213 --> 00:27:59,761
- Where did he go?
- He's gone.

426
00:27:59,761 --> 00:28:02,240
Let's go!

427
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:05,900
Grab your things.

428
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,760
Thank you so much, Uncle Ohn.

429
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:10,720
You're welcome.
See you later, sweetie.

430
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:11,880
Be careful.

431
00:28:13,947 --> 00:28:15,680
Come on, let's go home.

432
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:20,280
- Hello, Mom.
- Hello!

433
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:23,720
See you next week!

434
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:25,640
Bye-bye, Uncle Ohn!

435
00:28:27,632 --> 00:28:28,792
Roll up the window, dear.

436
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:46,889
What should I do now?

437
00:28:59,225 --> 00:29:00,720
There! There!

438
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:05,406
What are you laughing at?

439
00:29:05,980 --> 00:29:09,400
Look, it's all over my feed.

440
00:29:10,373 --> 00:29:11,373
What?

441
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:15,893
What's gotten into you,
watching cat and dog videos?

442
00:29:15,893 --> 00:29:17,367
They're just so cute.

443
00:29:17,367 --> 00:29:20,200
They just keep popping up.

444
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:23,130
Look, I can't stop.

445
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:27,640
They're so cute.

446
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:34,313
Let's have some tea.

447
00:29:49,803 --> 00:29:51,030
See?

448
00:29:51,030 --> 00:29:53,596
- Yeah, they're really cute.
- Right?

449
00:29:53,596 --> 00:29:55,656
Here, have some tea.

450
00:29:55,656 --> 00:29:57,735
- Ou...
- Careful.

451
00:29:57,735 --> 00:30:00,360
You're so sweet, babe.

452
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:03,160
Watch out, it's hot.

453
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:11,680
Look, my lenses are all fogged up.

454
00:30:13,474 --> 00:30:16,087
You can't see a thing.

455
00:30:16,944 --> 00:30:18,280
I've only just realized that

456
00:30:18,913 --> 00:30:20,120
raising a child

457
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:22,320
really does take

458
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:25,280
a whole village.

459
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:29,280
You mean Ikkyu's interview project?

460
00:30:30,089 --> 00:30:31,129
Mmm.

461
00:30:32,042 --> 00:30:36,520
Ikkyu is probably
the one having the most fun.

462
00:30:36,997 --> 00:30:39,202
That's probably true.

463
00:30:40,963 --> 00:30:41,963
All out.

464
00:31:02,697 --> 00:31:05,597
Should I put the chair here?

465
00:31:05,597 --> 00:31:07,600
- Right there is perfect.
- It's centered?

466
00:31:09,346 --> 00:31:11,291
Hey there, Ikkyu. I'm here!

467
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,280
- Hello, Uncle Kong.
- Hello, dear.

468
00:31:16,538 --> 00:31:17,880
Didn't Sky come with you?

469
00:31:18,320 --> 00:31:20,240
He's gone to camp, sweetie.

470
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:22,133
Thank you so much, Uncle Kong,

471
00:31:22,133 --> 00:31:24,480
for making time for his interview.

472
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,533
Oh, it's no trouble at all.

473
00:31:26,533 --> 00:31:28,087
Don't worry.

474
00:31:28,087 --> 00:31:30,560
When it comes to helping family,
just say the word.

475
00:31:31,300 --> 00:31:34,320
You know, Ikkyu...

476
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:38,360
I really love your project idea.

477
00:31:38,842 --> 00:31:42,760
"Once Upon A Dream,"
how did you come up with that?

478
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:44,263
You're only in 6th grade

479
00:31:44,263 --> 00:31:46,760
but you're already
making documentaries.

480
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:48,120
It's truly excellent.

481
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,520
Did you know that
when Ohn told me about it?

482
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:54,120
I agreed immediately.

483
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:58,080
- Thank you, Uncle Kong.
- My pleasure.

484
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:01,800
- Where should I sit? Here?
- Right there is great.

485
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:03,400
Alright.

486
00:32:04,853 --> 00:32:06,320
There we go.

487
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:08,560
I'll help film with another camera.

488
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,280
- Are you ready?
- Ready.

489
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:15,880
Landscape, Uncle Ohn.

490
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:17,520
Okay.

491
00:32:19,316 --> 00:32:23,383
When I was a kid,
I dreamed of being a merchant.

492
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:28,720
I wanted to sell things,
sell snacks in the market,

493
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:30,960
earn lots of money,
and then go home.

494
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:32,680
It seemed like fun.

495
00:32:34,186 --> 00:32:37,986
When I grew up,
I still loved sales.

496
00:32:37,986 --> 00:32:40,905
Only it changed to selling ideas.

497
00:32:41,939 --> 00:32:43,600
It's basically the same thing.

498
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:46,707
It's just a form of selling,
we've just changed the product.

499
00:32:46,707 --> 00:32:48,520
That's all.

500
00:32:50,840 --> 00:32:52,440
As for my other dream...

501
00:32:55,165 --> 00:32:57,640
I dreamed of being a father.

502
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:06,920
I wanted to know
what it's like to raise a child...

503
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:12,000
to love and care for someone

504
00:33:12,409 --> 00:33:15,249
until they grow up.
What would that feel like?

505
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:21,400
And now, I have a son.

506
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:23,520
Sky.

507
00:33:24,738 --> 00:33:26,440
I love him so much.

508
00:33:27,523 --> 00:33:30,800
He is truly a blessing of a son.

509
00:33:32,734 --> 00:33:36,793
And this is the dream
I am most happy about.

510
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:41,880
Because it's a dream that
I was able to make it come true.

511
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:45,880
"Uncle Kong is the most
open-minded person I've ever met."

512
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:49,080
"In Uncle Ohn's words,
he's big-hearted and generous."

513
00:33:49,349 --> 00:33:51,680
"Open to every opinion
and every possibility."

514
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:55,360
"I'm so happy that
he made his dream a reality."

515
00:33:55,818 --> 00:33:57,691
"Probably because
he's such an open person."

516
00:33:58,920 --> 00:33:59,920
Cut!

517
00:34:03,846 --> 00:34:04,846
Ohn.

518
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:09,320
If you ever want to have a child,
you just let me know.

519
00:34:10,120 --> 00:34:15,047
I'll be your consultant and
plan everything out for you.

520
00:34:15,047 --> 00:34:17,680
Easy to understand and stress-free.

521
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:22,520
I haven't thought that far ahead.

522
00:34:23,243 --> 00:34:24,880
"Just with this new project"

523
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:28,180
"I'm trying my absolute
best to nurture it,"

524
00:34:28,180 --> 00:34:31,175
"I'm not even sure
if I'll be able to keep it alive."

525
00:34:31,872 --> 00:34:35,545
No need to rush. Take your time.

526
00:34:35,545 --> 00:34:39,799
These days, there are
so many different options.

527
00:34:39,799 --> 00:34:43,200
Let's just say,
whenever you're ready, tell me.

528
00:34:43,200 --> 00:34:46,600
I'll set up the best plan for you.

529
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:48,760
Thank you.

530
00:35:02,520 --> 00:35:03,520
Hello?

531
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:06,200
I'm almost there.

532
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:10,920
Yeah, I got it.
Two cans of tuna in mineral water.

533
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:12,120
Okay, see you soon.

534
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:15,250
Oh!

535
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:19,200
Hey, you...

536
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:22,360
Are you waiting for me?

537
00:35:23,868 --> 00:35:26,894
We've run into
each other a lot lately.

538
00:35:30,204 --> 00:35:32,764
Come here, let me see.

539
00:35:33,977 --> 00:35:37,390
How are you doing?

540
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:41,760
Don't look at me like that,
my heart can't take it.

541
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:56,240
Hello, Jee.

542
00:35:58,760 --> 00:35:59,800
What is that?

543
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:04,160
What is it?

544
00:36:07,697 --> 00:36:08,697
What?

545
00:36:14,855 --> 00:36:16,040
Ta-da!

546
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:18,480
Hey!

547
00:36:19,730 --> 00:36:20,730
What!

548
00:36:20,901 --> 00:36:23,233
- A koala?
- Hmm!

549
00:36:23,233 --> 00:36:24,840
It's a cat.

550
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:28,120
I know it's a cat,
but why did you bring it up here?

551
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:31,473
You knew this condo forbids pets.

552
00:36:31,949 --> 00:36:35,240
Well, it was acting so sweet.

553
00:36:35,655 --> 00:36:38,408
Please let me stay with you.

554
00:36:38,408 --> 00:36:39,792
Let me stay. Please...

555
00:36:39,792 --> 00:36:41,474
- No!
- What?

556
00:36:41,993 --> 00:36:44,706
If the management finds out,
we're in trouble.

557
00:36:44,706 --> 00:36:47,280
Come on, everyone's doing it.

558
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:49,440
And does that make it
the right thing to do?

559
00:36:51,665 --> 00:36:54,665
I know it's breaking the rules.

560
00:36:55,096 --> 00:36:57,320
It's just temporary.

561
00:36:57,712 --> 00:36:59,719
Just until I can find it a home.

562
00:37:00,790 --> 00:37:02,672
Please, please?

563
00:37:02,697 --> 00:37:05,680
Please, please, please...
Look at him.

564
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:13,800
Don't be naughty. Look at that!

565
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:27,913
Please move the chair
to the right a bit.

566
00:37:27,913 --> 00:37:29,068
To the right?

567
00:37:29,446 --> 00:37:31,640
- A bit more.
- Okay, is this good?

568
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:33,360
Wow.

569
00:37:33,956 --> 00:37:36,720
You're really serious about this.
Quite a setup!

570
00:37:38,726 --> 00:37:40,300
Are you really
going to interview me?

571
00:37:40,638 --> 00:37:42,118
Most definitely.

572
00:37:51,650 --> 00:37:55,080
Take a deep breath.
Relax and don't be shy.

573
00:37:56,283 --> 00:37:57,283
Okay.

574
00:38:04,273 --> 00:38:05,273
Starting now?

575
00:38:06,288 --> 00:38:07,297
Action!

576
00:38:08,703 --> 00:38:10,720
When you were a kid,
what did you dream of being?

577
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:15,360
When I was little, I dreamed of
being a wealthy bachelorette.

578
00:38:17,744 --> 00:38:19,000
I wanted to live alone.

579
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:22,880
No marriage,
no need to take care of anyone.

580
00:38:23,749 --> 00:38:25,600
Just living a comfortable life.

581
00:38:26,294 --> 00:38:30,000
Traveling and dining
alone in fancy restaurants.

582
00:38:32,317 --> 00:38:35,080
Because I saw
how exhausted Grandma was.

583
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:39,360
She had to raise her kids alone,
and that really stuck with me.

584
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:46,320
But in the end, I got married,

585
00:38:47,520 --> 00:38:48,640
and I have a child.

586
00:38:52,534 --> 00:38:53,887
I was surprised.

587
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:59,240
Because I never thought
I could love someone this much.

588
00:39:01,843 --> 00:39:03,520
Love so deep it's hard to describe.

589
00:39:07,294 --> 00:39:09,560
But I also feel a bit guilty.

590
00:39:11,158 --> 00:39:12,200
About the fact...

591
00:39:13,388 --> 00:39:15,120
that my child
has to deal with the fact.

592
00:39:16,853 --> 00:39:18,280
His parents being separated.

593
00:39:22,132 --> 00:39:24,000
So I'm determined
to raise you well.

594
00:39:26,361 --> 00:39:27,921
To raise you to think for yourself.

595
00:39:28,833 --> 00:39:30,339
To know how to
make your own choices.

596
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:32,840
To be able to find happiness.

597
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:37,200
Is it working out
like that, Sweetie?

598
00:39:40,130 --> 00:39:41,160
Yes, Mom.

599
00:39:46,842 --> 00:39:48,000
Look at them.

600
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:51,080
I love you.

601
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:53,040
I love you too, Mom.

602
00:40:02,675 --> 00:40:04,941
"My Mom Aom is just the coolest."

603
00:40:06,323 --> 00:40:08,680
Alright, are you done filming?

604
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:10,320
I'll cook something for us.

605
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:38,146
You're hungry, aren't you?

606
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:42,560
Is this your favorite?

607
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:44,320
Mmm... there you go.

608
00:40:46,904 --> 00:40:48,840
Come here. Stop pacing around.

609
00:40:50,002 --> 00:40:52,002
Are you hungry?

610
00:40:53,480 --> 00:40:55,480
You're hissing at me?

611
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,380
I won't talk to you anymore.

612
00:41:00,351 --> 00:41:01,484
So serious.

613
00:41:13,678 --> 00:41:14,760
Thank you, dear.

614
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:17,960
The final scene,
I'll interview you. Okay?

615
00:41:18,568 --> 00:41:21,680
Ikkyu, finish chewing first,

616
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:23,320
before you speak.

617
00:41:24,853 --> 00:41:26,559
- Yes, Mom.
- Mmm.

618
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:32,108
Your shrimp paste chili
is as delicious as ever.

619
00:41:32,108 --> 00:41:33,240
Just a little spicy.

620
00:41:35,627 --> 00:41:36,627
Uncle Ohn?

621
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:39,200
Do you have anything
to use as a prop?

622
00:41:40,191 --> 00:41:41,224
Mmm.

623
00:41:41,224 --> 00:41:45,558
There are tons of cartoons
that he drew as a kid.

624
00:41:45,558 --> 00:41:47,880
I kept them in a box
in the storage room.

625
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:50,980
And I have a secret to tell you.

626
00:41:50,980 --> 00:41:52,164
What is it, Mom?

627
00:41:53,040 --> 00:41:55,480
He used to want to be a soldier.

628
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:01,065
- Really?
- Really.

629
00:42:01,637 --> 00:42:03,317
I want to see the pictures too!

630
00:42:03,317 --> 00:42:04,544
Those still exist, Mom?

631
00:42:04,569 --> 00:42:06,680
They do.
I kept a whole crate of them.

632
00:42:08,173 --> 00:42:10,480
Finish eating first,
then we can go look.

633
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:11,579
Mmm.

634
00:42:31,562 --> 00:42:34,192
Mom keeps lots of stuff here.

635
00:43:10,284 --> 00:43:12,600
When you were a kid,
what did you want to be, Uncle Ohn?

636
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:18,360
When I was little,
I dreamed of being a soldier.

637
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:23,648
I loved wearing the uniform;
it made me feel powerful.

638
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:28,160
Then why didn't you
become a soldier?

639
00:43:30,640 --> 00:43:33,720
Being a soldier would
probably have been okay.

640
00:43:34,567 --> 00:43:40,487
But I don't think
it really who I am.

641
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:44,200
I liked cartoons more.

642
00:43:45,184 --> 00:43:47,943
Once I read enough of them,
I started wanting to draw.

643
00:43:48,880 --> 00:43:52,960
And once I started drawing,
I couldn't stop.

644
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:54,680
I couldn't quit.

645
00:43:55,218 --> 00:43:56,438
I drew in notebooks,

646
00:43:56,438 --> 00:44:00,080
and I even drew on
the back of my homework sheets.

647
00:44:02,505 --> 00:44:03,545
Look at this.

648
00:44:05,917 --> 00:44:06,917
Here.

649
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:10,600
See this.

650
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:15,080
When you flip them fast, they move.

651
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:16,560
Watch, sweetie.

652
00:44:19,254 --> 00:44:20,760
You're so serious about this.

653
00:44:21,287 --> 00:44:22,484
Come to think of it,

654
00:44:22,484 --> 00:44:25,384
ever since I was little,
I've always seen you drawing.

655
00:44:26,159 --> 00:44:27,179
Mmm.

656
00:44:28,701 --> 00:44:32,623
Honestly, I never intended
for it to be my career.

657
00:44:33,724 --> 00:44:35,520
Looking back on it now,

658
00:44:36,068 --> 00:44:37,799
I think it probably
all started right there.

659
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:44,360
If I had to imagine myself
as a soldier today,

660
00:44:46,621 --> 00:44:48,174
I just can't see it at all.

661
00:44:51,868 --> 00:44:52,868
Cut!

662
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,480
How was it?

663
00:44:56,214 --> 00:44:57,214
It was great.

664
00:45:11,960 --> 00:45:14,173
My back is really starting to ache.

665
00:45:15,387 --> 00:45:16,859
- Mom.
- Hmm?

666
00:45:16,859 --> 00:45:19,459
I told you not to do it.
I'll do it myself.

667
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:25,725
Just a little bit here and there.
They say it's good exercise.

668
00:45:25,725 --> 00:45:27,320
Sure...

669
00:45:31,005 --> 00:45:33,465
"He lets me pet him now."

670
00:45:45,294 --> 00:45:47,080
I really want to know...

671
00:45:48,520 --> 00:45:50,480
What is your dream, Ikkyu?

672
00:45:51,906 --> 00:45:52,966
Mmm...

673
00:45:54,755 --> 00:45:56,115
I'm not really sure yet.

674
00:45:57,225 --> 00:45:59,480
Being a flight attendant
seems interesting.

675
00:46:00,939 --> 00:46:03,240
Being a writer
might be worth a try.

676
00:46:03,423 --> 00:46:05,320
Or being an interpreter
would be cool.

677
00:46:05,712 --> 00:46:09,985
I like wearing wigs and
doing dance covers for TikTok,

678
00:46:09,985 --> 00:46:12,040
and have people like them.
I do like that.

679
00:46:13,988 --> 00:46:16,001
Or being an influencer,
I think that would be good.

680
00:46:18,746 --> 00:46:21,106
Some days, I want to be a woman.

681
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:25,360
But then again, I'm scared.
I don't want surgery.

682
00:46:27,781 --> 00:46:30,667
You can just take your time
thinking about it.

683
00:46:32,066 --> 00:46:34,440
It's okay not to be sure.

684
00:46:35,738 --> 00:46:37,431
If you want to do many things,

685
00:46:37,431 --> 00:46:40,760
you just have to
dive in and try them out.

686
00:46:42,258 --> 00:46:45,240
Dreams can always change.

687
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:47,271
And so can your identity.

688
00:46:48,360 --> 00:46:50,880
You don't have to
rush into any decisions.

689
00:46:51,642 --> 00:46:55,640
Okay. I'm going to try
doing everything I want to do.

690
00:46:57,814 --> 00:46:58,814
Excellent.

691
00:47:06,186 --> 00:47:08,240
Mom, look at that!

692
00:47:09,619 --> 00:47:11,800
Oh wow...

693
00:47:13,360 --> 00:47:15,640
First thing, though.

694
00:47:15,939 --> 00:47:18,760
Shouldn't you finish the editing?

695
00:47:19,756 --> 00:47:23,648
Yes! I have to finish editing
and make everyone go "Bravo!"

696
00:47:26,645 --> 00:47:28,160
Still dancing?

697
00:47:28,859 --> 00:47:30,000
I'll dance with you then.

698
00:47:43,400 --> 00:47:46,000
Next up is Ikkyu's.

699
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:49,840
It's a solo project that
he had put a lot of effort into.

700
00:47:50,320 --> 00:47:51,840
I'm quite excited myself.

701
00:47:55,446 --> 00:47:57,880
"Ikkyu the Psycho Sissy.
Let's not play with him."

702
00:47:58,566 --> 00:47:59,593
"Ban Ikkyu!"

703
00:47:59,593 --> 00:48:05,580
"Ban Ikkyu! Ban Ikkyu!"

704
00:48:05,580 --> 00:48:06,985
Ikkyu, the floor is yours.

705
00:48:29,664 --> 00:48:32,096
"When I was little,
I loved traditional dance."

706
00:48:32,096 --> 00:48:33,731
"I wanted to be a star."

707
00:48:33,731 --> 00:48:36,360
"I wanted to be
a national volleyball player."

708
00:48:36,960 --> 00:48:38,440
"Take my team to the Olympics."

709
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:41,840
"At first, I just wanted to know"

710
00:48:42,344 --> 00:48:44,120
"what adults dreamed of
when they were kids."

711
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:47,480
"What they wanted to be,
and if they actually became that."

712
00:48:48,240 --> 00:48:49,880
"But after listening
to so many of them,"

713
00:48:49,880 --> 00:48:53,593
"I started to feel that
dreams can change."

714
00:48:53,593 --> 00:48:55,993
"Some dreams never got started."

715
00:48:55,993 --> 00:48:58,740
"Some dreams remain,
just in a different shape."

716
00:48:58,740 --> 00:49:01,326
"And some people find new dreams
over and over again."

717
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:07,160
"No matter how a dream changes
or what form it takes,"

718
00:49:07,520 --> 00:49:10,360
"the adults I interviewed
were determined and brave."

719
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:13,360
"Because everyone has a 'backup'
at least one person."

720
00:49:13,876 --> 00:49:17,439
"This backup is what brings
dreams closer to reality."

721
00:49:46,480 --> 00:49:48,320
"Hey, from now on,"

722
00:49:48,320 --> 00:49:50,680
"I might not have to do
group projects all by myself."

723
00:49:51,320 --> 00:49:55,600
"My next dream is to collect
good friends like Uncle Ohn."

724
00:50:05,320 --> 00:50:07,193
"I once dreamed of
being a good teacher."

725
00:50:07,193 --> 00:50:09,087
"Better than the ones
I encountered."

726
00:50:09,087 --> 00:50:12,000
"I will be a teacher who
is open-minded and sincere."

727
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:14,560
"Encourage them
to learn for themselves."

728
00:50:18,840 --> 00:50:21,560
"I dreamed of growing up
to be a beautiful woman,"

729
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:24,040
"to have a warm, happy family."

730
00:50:24,040 --> 00:50:25,840
"It would be so wonderful."

731
00:50:25,840 --> 00:50:27,800
"Thanks, Ohn, for dreaming of me."

732
00:50:29,640 --> 00:50:31,800
"Kit! Wait up!"

733
00:50:32,392 --> 00:50:34,360
"Kittima! Kit..."

734
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:42,520
Bye-bye, Kittima.

735
00:51:09,358 --> 00:51:12,268
Mom is incredibly good
at keeping things.

736
00:51:54,157 --> 00:51:57,320
Alright, let's give it another go.

737
00:52:35,800 --> 00:52:37,080
Hey, who's this?

738
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:40,320
Coming to greet me?
What are you doing right here?

739
00:52:41,008 --> 00:52:42,995
What are you up to?

740
00:52:42,995 --> 00:52:44,888
Here... right here.

741
00:52:45,320 --> 00:52:48,400
Look at you,
greeting me at the door?

742
00:52:49,688 --> 00:52:52,480
Why are you
sitting here in the dark?

743
00:52:55,315 --> 00:52:58,200
Ah... yeah.

744
00:52:59,760 --> 00:53:01,080
Have you eaten yet?

745
00:53:07,132 --> 00:53:10,005
- I completely lost track of time.
- Mmm.

746
00:53:10,005 --> 00:53:11,040
Oh!

747
00:53:11,608 --> 00:53:15,663
Is the job interview finished?
Are you tired?

748
00:53:16,077 --> 00:53:19,108
Exhausted. But I'm okay.

749
00:53:23,152 --> 00:53:24,152
Oh!

750
00:53:26,546 --> 00:53:27,800
This is really nice.

751
00:53:32,040 --> 00:53:35,024
Mmm, so cute.

752
00:53:36,338 --> 00:53:40,018
Where are you going?
You were just greeting me.

753
00:53:40,340 --> 00:53:43,520
- Come here, you!
- Charcoal.

754
00:53:43,880 --> 00:53:47,840
What kind of creature are you?

755
00:53:48,200 --> 00:53:52,480
At first I didn't want a pet,
but now, I'm loving it.

756
00:53:52,997 --> 00:53:54,604
Love you.

757
00:53:55,552 --> 00:53:59,480
Does that mean Charcoal doesn't
have to find a new home anymore?

758
00:54:00,920 --> 00:54:03,720
He has already chosen to stay here.

759
00:54:04,200 --> 00:54:06,280
Who can do
anything about it, right?

760
00:54:07,122 --> 00:54:08,640
Nothing we can do.

761
00:54:10,665 --> 00:54:12,440
I'm happy for you, kiddo.

762
00:54:13,606 --> 00:54:14,680
Stay with...

763
00:54:15,614 --> 00:54:17,440
Papa Jee and Daddy Ohn, okay?

764
00:54:19,911 --> 00:54:22,200
He's letting you stay.
No need to look for a new home.

765
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:23,238
We'll be together.

766
00:54:23,238 --> 00:54:24,800
Isn't it beautiful?

767
00:54:24,825 --> 00:54:26,666
Let me show you.

768
00:54:28,973 --> 00:54:29,980
No?

769
00:54:31,659 --> 00:54:34,240
- Beautiful.
- Oh, beautiful.

770
00:54:35,066 --> 00:54:36,320
It's beautiful, isn't it?

771
00:54:46,400 --> 00:54:48,520
"Tonight,
the two of us will sleep soundly."

772
00:54:49,800 --> 00:54:53,160
"Maybe it's the happiness
of taking care of Charcoal."

773
00:54:54,000 --> 00:54:56,247
"Or maybe it's because
our hearts are full"

774
00:54:56,247 --> 00:54:59,105
"when old dreams drop by
for a visit on a weary day."

775
00:55:00,415 --> 00:55:01,695
"Whatever the reason"

776
00:55:02,727 --> 00:55:05,720
"tonight, I'll fall asleep
with a little new dream"

777
00:55:06,357 --> 00:55:08,284
"that feels like
it's beginning once again."

778
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:10,966
"Goodnight, everyone."

779
00:55:46,280 --> 00:55:48,000
It's terminal liver cancer.

780
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:49,906
- Not true!
- Not true!

781
00:55:51,480 --> 00:55:53,280
You're sick but
still walking around?

782
00:55:53,680 --> 00:55:55,280
Didn't the doctor tell you not to?

783
00:55:56,960 --> 00:55:58,400
What if, between the two of us...

784
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:01,640
one of us has to go first,

785
00:56:01,640 --> 00:56:03,480
and leaves the other

786
00:56:03,920 --> 00:56:05,200
completely alone in this world?

787
00:56:06,100 --> 00:56:11,200
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

788
00:56:11,200 --> 00:56:14,073
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

789
00:56:14,073 --> 00:56:16,620
Subtitle by Trirat Trakulphat
